article.headline: Adam Clark scores last 4 points, finishes with 29 to lead Merrimack over Stonehill 66-63
article.description: — Adam Clark scored the last four points and finished with 29 points Merrimack's 66-63 victory against Stonehill on Thursday night for its seventh straight win.
article.linkText: Adam Clark scores last 4 points, finishes with 29 to lead Merrimack over Stonehill 66-63
article.story: SOUTH EASTON, Mass. -- — Adam Clark scored the last four points and finished with 29 points Merrimack's 66-63 victory against Stonehill on Thursday night for its seventh straight win. Clark's jumper with nine seconds left gave Merrimack a 64-63 lead. He added two free throws to seal it. Clark also had six assists for the Warriors (16-10, 10-2 Northeast Conference). Bryan Etumnu added nine points, seven rebounds and five blocks. Samba Diallo finished with eight points. Max Zegarowski led the way for the Skyhawks (3-24, 1-11) with 19 points and six rebounds. Tony Felder added 12 points, eight rebounds and two steals for Stonehill. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
